Note:
MIPS64 (n64) Linux Syscall ABI

This file implements Linux MIPS64 (n64 ABI) system calls for the Runa compiler.

Platform-specific details:
- Platform: Linux MIPS64
- Syscall mechanism: syscall instruction
- Syscall number register: $v0 ($2)
- Argument registers: $a0-$a7 ($4-$11), additional args on stack
- Return value: $v0 ($2)
- Error indication: $a3 ($7) set to 1 on error, $v0 contains errno

Linux MIPS64 syscall convention:
- $v0 = syscall number (5000+ range for MIPS64)
- $a0-$a7 = arguments 1-8 (8 args in registers!)
- Args 9+ go on stack
- syscall instruction triggers kernel
- $v0 = return value (or errno if $a3 == 1)

MIPS64 syscall numbers differ from other architectures (5000+ base).
This file provides both syscall number constants and wrapper functions.

MIPS64-specific notes:
- Uses mmap (not mmap2) for 64-bit offset support
- Error handling via $a3 register (like MIPS32)
- 8 argument registers (unlike MIPS32's 4)

Dependencies: None (uses inline assembly for syscalls)
:End Note

Note: Linux MIPS64 syscall numbers (different from MIPS32)

