Note: File mode constants (POSIX permission bits)
Process called "mips64_MODE_0644" returns Integer:
    Note: POSIX file mode 0644 = rw-r--r-- (owner read/write, group/other read).
    Note: Octal 0644 = decimal 420 = 0x1A4 = S_IRUSR | S_IWUSR | S_IRGRP | S_IROTH.
    Note: Source: POSIX <sys/stat.h>; identical across MIPS Linux and asm-generic.
    Return 420
End Process

Process called "mips64_MODE_0755" returns Integer:
